&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here at North Devon, we are looking for an expert autonomous practitioner to work in the breast imaging department as an Advanced Practitioner Mammographer for a fixed term of 12 months to cover maternity leave.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would expect the candidate to have extensive knowledge and experience in mammographic film reading, breast ultrasound and ultrasound-guided breast intervention including core biopsy, aspirations, wire localisations, clip marker insertions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The breast imaging service operates over 2-3 days, offering symptomatic breast clinics, and booked appointments for symptomatic follow up and family history mammograms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that we may close this vacancy early if we receive a high volume of applicants.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 15/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**As this post is in a shortage occupation code it qualifies for the Trust’s Recommend a Friend Scheme, please find further information on the attached link**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
